        "timestamp": "2017-09-05 19:48:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDan, it looks like when you enable unit tests on this repo, the unit tests themselves are now failing. I can fix the cause of the failing unit test in this patch but it seems like 1) That might be better done in another patch 2) We should have unit tests running in verify as soon as possible so that we don't let more failures get merged. Thoughts?",
        "patchset_number": 1
